{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH7Hs9dc2Kzvjr5Tn6JU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. All 3 tests pass, including the new regression test.\n\n**Root cause:** in `src/validate.js`, the domain-label group was `(\\.[A-Za-z0-9-]*)*` — the `*` on the label body allowed an *empty* label, so `mail..example` parsed as `mail` + `.` (empty label) + `.example`. Consecutive dots slipped through.\n\n**Fix:** changed that quantifier to `+`, requiring every label to have at least one character:\n\n```js\n/^[^\\s@]+@[A-Za-z0-9-]+(\\.[A-Za-z0-9-]+)*\\.[A-Za-z]{2,}$/\n```\n\nNow `user@mail..example.com` is rejected while normal addresses like `ada@example.com` still pass. I also added a regression test pinning the reported bounce case."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":319,"cache_read_input_tokens":23629,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":319},"output_tokens":6,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b6e27f06-ddcb-4743-883e-3c9fe81a1edb","uuid":"7b3f84fd-3693-479e-83be-1bcac2e31bfc","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:38:34.041Z","request_id":"req_011CdH7HqgKr1MBzn3DJgNdA"}
